definition.value: A pyrimidine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside having cytosine as the nucleobase.
A glycosylglucose consisting of an alpha-D-xylopyranose residue and a F-glucopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
A dTDP-sugar having alpha-D-glucopyranose as the sugar portion.
The trans isomer of the L-proline peptide bond.
